It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#6495ED"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Correct

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#6495ED"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Correct	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Correct	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#6495ED"><br/></td> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" bgcolor="#E0E0E0"><br/></td> </tr><tr> <td style="border-top: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Correct	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-left: 1px solid #E0E0E0; border-right: 1px solid #E0E0E0" colspan="29" bgcolor="#E0E0E0" height="10"></td> </tr> </table> <h6>Background</h6><p>Restriction Fragment Length Polymorphism (RFLP) is a molecular biology method used to differentiate between closely related DNA samples. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Incorrect	C. Suspect &num;3	Correct	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect

It is often used in forensic investigations.</p> <h6>Disclaimer</h6><p>In adherence to the principles of due process, all individuals in this exercise shall be presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt in a court of law.</p> <h6>Instructions</h6><p>Examine the provided DNA gel profile to identify which suspect is responsible for leaving the blood sample. Each band in the gel signifies a DNA fragment. The killer's DNA will match with the blood sample found at the crime scene.</p>	A. Suspect &num;1	Incorrect	B. Suspect &num;2	Correct	C. Suspect &num;3	Incorrect	D. Suspect &num;4	Incorrect
